                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="78621" author="adilger" created="Thu, 6 Mar 2014 18:57:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A fix for this was landed via &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/8057&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/8057&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3527&quot; title=&quot;UID/GID Mapping&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3527&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3527&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="75878" author="adilger" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2014 18:27:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Joshua, this is the problem that I pointed out in the most recent patch.  The 2.6 client (with the 2.6 test scripts) is trying to run the nodemap commands against a 2.5 server, which does not understand them.  This needs a check like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        [ $(lustre_version_code $SINGLEMDS) -lt $(version_code 2.5.53) ] &amp;amp;&amp;amp;
                skip &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;MDS does not support nodemap&quot;&lt;/span&gt; &amp;amp;&amp;amp; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
